{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-jsx","path":"/blog/20210130-designing-games-book/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Artem Demo, indie developer","author":"Artem Demo"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"621521bf-4cfd-590b-9931-a010cf257c7d","excerpt":"Lately I finished the “Designing Games”, by Tynan Sylvester, lead developer of Rimworld.\nHighly recommend to everyone who is interested in game design.\nThis book is not about the code, but about experience that your game will create.","html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 333px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/24ae2c5b68e0466fa55da558162a7a97/570e8/designing-games.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 150%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Designing Games, by Tynan Sylvester\"\n        title=\"Designing Games, by Tynan Sylvester\"\n        src=\"/static/24ae2c5b68e0466fa55da558162a7a97/570e8/designing-games.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/24ae2c5b68e0466fa55da558162a7a97/6aa9a/designing-games.jpg 148w,\n/static/24ae2c5b68e0466fa55da558162a7a97/3e520/designing-games.jpg 295w,\n/static/24ae2c5b68e0466fa55da558162a7a97/570e8/designing-games.jpg 333w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 333px) 100vw, 333px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Lately I finished the “Designing Games”, by Tynan Sylvester, lead developer of Rimworld.\nHighly recommend to everyone who is interested in game design.\nThis book is not about the code, but about experience that your game will create. </p>\n<!-- end -->\n<p>Not sure if I have something to add to this short statement.\nBut I have some nice examples of author ideas he used in his games:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><em>GAME DESIGN isn’t in code, art, or sound. It’s not in sculpting game pieces or painting game boards. Game design means crafting the rules that make those pieces come alive.</em></p>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p><em>If you want a metaphor to use while thinking about games, don’t think of stories or movies. … Instead, think of a game as a strange kind of machine—an engine of experience.</em></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>And one of the best statements and paradoxes for the perfectionists out there:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><em>In game design, temporarily accepting poor-quality work ultimately leads to better-quality work. This is the PARADOX OF QUALITY.</em></p>\n</blockquote>","frontmatter":{"title":"Designing Games, book by Tynan Sylvester","date":"January 30, 2021","tags":["book","studying","game"]}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/20210130-designing-games-book/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/20210128-vertical-lines-between-tiles/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Vertical lines between tiles in tile map in unity","tags":["unity","tiles"]}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/20210201-2d-platformer-explosion-wave-in-unity/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"2D explosion wave in unity","tags":["unity","game"]}}}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}